{
  "message": "[review-fix](fuzz): seed corpus for ft_serialize_state_dict target\n\nCross-review of 42945e2 (the ft-serialize state dict fuzz target)\nfound that no seed corpus was committed. load_state_dict_from_bytes\nfails fast with InvalidMagic on any input that does not start with\nthe 4-byte FTSV literal, so a coverage-guided fuzzer starting from\nzero seeds has to discover those four bytes by random byte mutation\n(infeasible) before any of the rest of the parser is exercised.\n\nAdd four mechanically-constructed seeds covering the dispatch table\nintroduced by d6b96f7 (frankentorch-sre):\n\n  5fb7eb5b  16 B  empty state dict (num_tensors=0)\n  46e8f8b5  46 B  one F32 scalar (dtype_tag=1)\n  f570bd1a  46 B  one F16 [2] tensor (dtype_tag=2)\n  0b114b15  46 B  one BF16 [2] tensor (dtype_tag=3)\n\nEach seed was generated with the exact byte layout that\nencode_state_dict_to_bytes produces (FT_MAGIC | version u32 LE |\nnum_tensors u64 LE | per-tensor records). Filenames are sha1 of\ncontents per cargo-fuzz / libfuzzer convention. ft-serialize 66\ntests still pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
